nodes.label: Glioma
nodes.def: The presence of a glioma, which is a neoplasm of the central nervous system originating from a glial cell (astrocytes or oligodendrocytes).

nodes.label: Abnormal antihelix morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the antihelix.

nodes.label: Osteolytic defects of the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Dissolution or degeneration of bone tissue of the phalanges of the hand.

nodes.label: Symphalangism affecting the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Fusion of two or more phalangeal bones of the hand.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the extraocular muscles
nodes.def: An abnormality of an extraocular muscle.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the crus of the helix
nodes.def: An abnormality of the crus of the helix, which is the horizontal piece of cartilage located outside the ear canal that divides the upper and lower parts of the ear.

nodes.label: Duplication of phalanx of hand
nodes.def: This term applies if one or more of the phalanges of the hand are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

nodes.label: Duplication of the middle phalanx of hand
nodes.def: This term applies if one or more of the middle phalanges of the hand are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

nodes.label: Short metacarpal
nodes.def: Diminished length of one or more metacarpal bones in relation to the others of the same hand or to the contralateral metacarpal.

nodes.label: Patchy sclerosis of toe phalanx
nodes.def: Uneven (irregular) increase in bone density of one or more of the phalanges of the foot.

nodes.label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the distal phalanges of the toes
nodes.def: Absence or underdevelopment of the distal phalanges of the toes.

nodes.label: Absent epiphyses of the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Absence of one or more epiphyses of the phalanges of the fingers.

nodes.label: Bracket epiphyses of the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Bracket epiphysis refers to an abnormality in which the epiphysis surrounds a phalangeal bone, having a bracket-like form and reaching from the proximal side of a phalanx to the distal side.

nodes.label: Enlarged epiphyses of the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Abnormally large size of the epiphyses of the phalanges of the fingers with respect to age-dependent norms.

nodes.label: Fragmentation of the epiphyses of the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Fragmented appearance of the epiphyses of the phalanges of the fingers.

nodes.label: Irregular epiphyses of the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Irregular radiographic opacity of the epiphyses of the phalanges of the fingers.

nodes.label: Pseudoepiphyses of the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: A secondary ossification center in the phalanges of the hand that is distinct from the normal epiphysis that does not contribute to the longitudinal growth of a tubular bone.

nodes.label: Small epiphyses of the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Abnormally small size of the epiphyses of the phalanges of the fingers with respect to age-dependent norms.

nodes.label: Triangular epiphyses of the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: A triangular appearance of the epiphyses of the phalanges of the fingers of the hand.

nodes.label: Absent toe
nodes.def: Aplasia of a toe. That is, absence of all phalanges of a non-hallux digit of the foot and the associated soft tissues.

nodes.label: Abnormal hair quantity
nodes.def: An abnormal amount of hair.

nodes.label: Epidermal thickening
nodes.def: Thickening of the epidermal layer of the skin.

nodes.label: Abnormal cerebral artery morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of a cerebral artery. The cerebral arteries comprise three main pairs of arteries and their branches, which supply the cerebrum of the brain. These are the anterior cerebral artery, the middle cerebral artery, and the posterior cerebral artery.

nodes.label: Short finger
nodes.def: Abnormally short finger associated with developmental hypoplasia.

nodes.label: Abnormal urinary color
nodes.def: An abnormal color of the urine, that is, the color of the urine appears different from the usual straw-yellow color.

nodes.label: Abnormal megakaryocyte morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of megakaryocytes. Mature blood platelets are released from the cytoplasm of megakaryocytes, which are bone-marrow resident cells.

nodes.label: Abnormality of von Willebrand factor
nodes.def: Decreased quantity or activity of von Willebrand factor. Von Willebrand factor mediates the adhesion of platelets to the collagen exposed on endothelial cell surfaces.

nodes.label: Oligosacchariduria
nodes.def: Increased urinary excretion of oligosaccharides (low molecular weight carbohydrate chains composed of at least three monosaccharide subunits), derived from a partial degradation of glycoproteins.

nodes.label: Abnormal thalamus morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the thalamus.

nodes.label: Increased circulating immunoglobulin concentration
nodes.def: An increased level of gamma globulin (immunoglobulin) in the blood.

nodes.label: Skin appendage neoplasm
nodes.def: A benign or malignant neoplasm that arises from the hair follicles, sebaceous glands, or sweat glands.

nodes.label: Abnormality of digestive system physiology
nodes.def: A functional anomaly of the digestive system.

nodes.label: Focal emotional seizure
nodes.def: Seizures presenting with an emotion or the appearance of having an emotion as an early prominent feature, such as fear, spontaneous joy or euphoria, laughing (gelastic), or crying, (dacrystic). These emotional seizures may occur with or without objective clinical signs of a seizure evident to the observer.

nodes.label: Abnormal wrist morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the wrist.

nodes.label: Abnormality of pulmonary circulation
nodes.def: A functional anomaly of that portion of the cardiosvascular system that carries deoxygenated blood from the heart to the lungs and returns oxygenated blood back to the heart.

nodes.label: Abnormal reproductive system morphology
nodes.def: A structural or developmental anomaly of any of the tissues involved in the genital system.

nodes.label: Reduced social responsiveness
nodes.def: A reduced ability to participate in the back-and-forth flow of social interaction appropriate to culture and developmental level, which is normally characterized by an influence of the behavior of one person on the behavior of another person. This results in difficulty interacting with others through emotional, physical, or verbal communication.

nodes.label: Focal aware sensory seizure
nodes.def: A focal sensory seizure during which awareness is retained throughout the seizure.

nodes.label: Focal impaired awareness sensory seizure
nodes.def: A focal sensory seizure in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating proteinogenic amino acid derivative concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration in the blood circulation of a compound that is derived from an amino acid.

nodes.label: Abnormal pharynx morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the pharynx.

nodes.label: Abnormal urinary purine level
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal amount of a purine compound in the urine. Purines are aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a purine moiety, which is formed a pyrimidine-ring ring fused to an imidazole ring. Two of the four deoxyribonucleotides (deoxyadenosine and deoxyguanosine) and two of the four ribonucleotides (adenosine, or AMP, and guanosine, or GMP) are purines.

nodes.label: Abnormal fetal cardiovascular physiology
nodes.def: Abnormal functionality of the fetal cardiovascular system.

nodes.label: Appendicular spasticity
nodes.def: A type of spasticity that affects one or more limbs (arms or legs).

nodes.label: Positive stool infectious agent test
nodes.def: Any kind of test for an infectious agent in stool positive.

nodes.label: Abnormal dermis morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the dermis, the layer of skin that lies beneath the epidermis and above the subcutaneous layer.

nodes.label: Generalized-onset motor seizure
nodes.def: A generalized motor seizure is a type of generalized-onset seizure with predominantly motor (involving musculature) signs. The motor event could consist of an increase (positive) or decrease (negative) in muscle contraction to produce a movement.

nodes.label: Abnormal cervical spine morphology
nodes.def: Any morphological abnormality of the cervical vertebral column.

nodes.label: Neoplasm of the breast
nodes.def: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the breast.

nodes.label: Abnormality of skin physiology
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the physiological function of the skin.

nodes.label: Fractured carpal bone
nodes.def: A partial or complete breakage of the carpal bone.

nodes.label: Bloodstream antibacterial antibody positivity
nodes.def: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a bacterium.

nodes.label: Abnormal CSF carboxylic acid concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a carboxylic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid.

nodes.label: Anti-ganglioside antibody positivity
nodes.def: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react to gangliosides.

nodes.label: Triggered by exposure to medication
nodes.def: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by administration of a medication.

nodes.label: Nutrition history
nodes.def: A part of the past medical history consisting of information about the typical food intake of an individual.

nodes.label: Triggered by food ingestion
nodes.def: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by eating a certain food.

nodes.label: Anti-coagulation factor antibody positivity
nodes.def: The presence of an antibody in the blood circulation that is directed against a coagulation factor.

nodes.label: Camptodactyly of finger
nodes.def: The distal interphalangeal joint and/or the proximal interphalangeal joint of the fingers cannot be extended to 180 degrees by either active or passive extension.

nodes.label: Inflammatory abnormality of the eye
nodes.def: Inflammation of the eye, parts of the eye or the periorbital region.

nodes.label: Telangiectasia of the skin
nodes.def: Presence of small, permanently dilated blood vessels near the surface of the skin, visible as small focal red lesions.

nodes.label: Abnormal cerebral vascular morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the cerebral blood vessels.

nodes.label: Abnormal eating behavior
nodes.def: Abnormal eating habits involve excessive or insufficient consumption of food, or any other abnormal pattern of food consumption.

nodes.label: Abnormal female external genitalia morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the female external genitalia.

nodes.label: Abnormality of reproductive system physiology
nodes.def: An abnormal functionality of the genital system.

nodes.label: Exotropia
nodes.def: A form of strabismus with one or both eyes deviated outward.

nodes.label: Abnormal choroid morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the choroid.

nodes.label: Abnormal diminished volition
nodes.def: A reduction in willful and motivated goal-directed behavior that is considered the determinant of behavior and adaptation that allows individuals to get started, be energized to perform a sustained and directed action.

nodes.label: Platyspondyly
nodes.def: A flattened vertebral body shape with reduced distance between the vertebral endplates.

nodes.label: Hyperpigmentation of the skin
nodes.def: A darkening of the skin related to an increase in melanin production and deposition.

nodes.label: Skin rash
nodes.def: A red eruption of the skin.

nodes.label: Hypertrichosis
nodes.def: Hypertrichosis is increased hair growth that is abnormal in quantity or location.

nodes.label: Abnormal nasal septum morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the nasal septum.

nodes.label: Abnormal nasal bridge morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the nasal bridge, which is the saddle-shaped area that includes the nasal root and the lateral aspects of the nose. It lies between the glabella and the inferior boundary of the nasal bone, and extends laterally to the inner canthi.

nodes.label: Abnormal foveal morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the fovea centralis, the central area of the macula that mediates central, high resolution vision and contains the largest concentration of cone cells in the retina.

nodes.label: Abnormal lens morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the lens.

nodes.label: Abnormal left ventricle morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the left ventricle of the heart.

nodes.label: Thrombocytopenia
nodes.def: A reduction in the number of circulating thrombocytes.

nodes.label: Hypoglycemia
nodes.def: A decreased concentration of glucose in the blood.

nodes.label: Abnormal thrombosis
nodes.def: Venous or arterial thrombosis (formation of blood clots) of spontaneous nature and which cannot be fully explained by acquired risk (e.g. atherosclerosis).

nodes.label: Diarrhea
nodes.def: Abnormally increased frequency (usually defined as three or more) loose or watery bowel movements a day.

nodes.label: Abdominal pain
nodes.def: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) and perceived to originate in the abdomen.

nodes.label: Dyspnea
nodes.def: Difficult or labored breathing. Dyspnea is a subjective feeling only the patient can rate, e.g., on a Borg scale.

nodes.label: Intracranial hemorrhage
nodes.def: Hemorrhage occurring within the skull.

nodes.label: Abnormal duodenum morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the duodenum, i.e., the first section of the small intestine.

nodes.label: Corneal dystrophy
nodes.def: The term corneal dystrophy embraces a heterogenous group of bilateral genetically determined non-inflammatory corneal diseases that are restricted to the cornea.

nodes.label: Distal symphalangism of hands
nodes.def: The term distal symphalangism refers to a bony fusion of the distal and middle phalanges of the digits of the hand, in other words the distal interphalangeal joint (DIJ) is missing which can be seen either on x-rays or as an absence of the distal interphalangeal finger creases.

nodes.label: Spasticity
nodes.def: A motor disorder characterized by a velocity-dependent increase in tonic stretch reflexes with increased muscle tone, exaggerated (hyperexcitable) tendon reflexes.

nodes.label: Dystonia
nodes.def: An abnormally increased muscular tone that causes fixed abnormal postures. There is a slow, intermittent twisting motion that leads to exaggerated turning and posture of the extremities and trunk.

nodes.label: Hyperreflexia
nodes.def: Hyperreflexia is the presence of hyperactive stretch reflexes of the muscles.

nodes.label: Abnormal hip joint morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the hip joint.

nodes.label: Cardiomyopathy
nodes.def: A myocardial disorder in which the heart muscle is structurally and functionally abnormal, in the absence of coronary artery disease, hypertension, valvular disease and congenital heart disease sufficient to cause the observed myocardial abnormality.

nodes.label: Abnormal 5th finger morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality affecting one or both 5th fingers.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the abdominal wall
nodes.def: The presence of any abnormality affecting the abdominal wall.

nodes.label: Abnormal anterior eye segment morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the anterior segment of the eyeball (which comprises the structures in front of the vitreous humor: the cornea, iris, ciliary body, and lens).

nodes.label: Abnormal lymphocyte morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of lymphocytes.

nodes.label: Abnormality of acid-base homeostasis
nodes.def: An abnormality of the balance or maintenance of the balance of acids and bases in bodily fluids, resulting in an abnormal pH.

nodes.label: Reduced consciousness
nodes.def: Abnormally diminished level of attention, responsiveness, or wakefulness.

nodes.label: Hematological neoplasm
nodes.def: Neoplasms located in the blood and blood-forming tissue (the bone marrow and lymphatic tissue).

nodes.label: Abnormal ilium morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the ilium, the largest and uppermost bone of the pelvis.

nodes.label: Neoplasm of the pancreas
nodes.def: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the pancreas.

nodes.label: Neoplasm of the liver
nodes.def: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the liver.

nodes.label: Granulomatosis
nodes.def: A granulomatous inflammation leading to multiple granuloma formation, which is a specific type of inflammation. A granuloma is a focal compact collection of inflammatory cells, mononuclear cells predominating, usually as a result of the persistence of a non-degradable product and of active cell mediated hypersensitivity.

nodes.label: Short long bone
nodes.def: One or more abnormally short long bone.

nodes.label: Abnormal cortical bone morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of compact bone (also known as cortical bone), which forms the dense surface of bones.

nodes.label: Arterial calcification
nodes.def: Pathological deposition of calcium salts in one or more arteries.

nodes.label: Decreased circulating alkaline phosphatase activity
nodes.def: Concentration or activity of alkaline phosphatase outside the upper or lower limtis of normal in the blood circulation.

nodes.label: Short middle phalanx of finger
nodes.def: Short (hypoplastic) middle phalanx of finger, affecting one or more fingers.

nodes.label: Flexion contracture of toe
nodes.def: One or more bent (flexed) toe joints that cannot be straightened actively or passively.

nodes.label: Abnormal cardiac atrium morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of a cardiac atrium.

nodes.label: Abnormal left ventricular function
nodes.def: Inability of the left ventricle to perform its normal physiologic function. Failure is either due to an inability to contract the left ventricle or the inability to relax completely and fill with blood during diastole.

nodes.label: Abnormal alveolar ridge morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the alveolar ridges (on the upper or lower jaws). The alveolar ridges contain the sockets (alveoli) of the teeth.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the hepatic vasculature
nodes.def: An abnormality of the hepatic vasculature.

nodes.label: Neoplasm of the stomach
nodes.def: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the stomach.

nodes.label: Atrophy/Degeneration affecting the cerebrum
nodes.def: The presence of atrophy (wasting) of the cerebrum, also known as the telencephalon, the largest and most highly developed part of the human brain.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the vasculature
nodes.def: An abnormality of the vasculature.

nodes.label: Abnormal talus morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the talus.

nodes.label: Abnormal toenail morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the toenail.

nodes.label: Antinuclear antibody positivity
nodes.def: The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react against nuclei or nuclear components.

nodes.label: Onset
nodes.def: The age group in which disease manifestations appear.

nodes.label: Skeletal muscle hypertrophy
nodes.def: Abnormal increase in muscle size and mass not due to training.

nodes.label: Finger symphalangism
nodes.def: An abnormal union between bones or parts of bones of the fingers. The synonymous term "symphalangism of the hand" may be translated as fusions of bones of varying digree, that involve at least one phalangeal bone of the hand. If bony fusions are referred to as "Symphalangism" the fusion occurs in a proximo-distal axis. Fusions of bones of the fingers in a radio-ulnar axis are referred to as "bony" Syndactyly.

nodes.label: Bullet-shaped phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: The presence of short and wide phalanges which taper distally ("bullet shaped").

nodes.label: Short thumb
nodes.def: Hypoplasia (congenital reduction in size) of the thumb.

nodes.label: Anomaly of the upper limb diaphyses
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of a diaphysis of the arm.

nodes.label: Limb undergrowth
nodes.def: Limb shortening because of underdevelopment of one or more bones of the extremities.

nodes.label: Sparse hair
nodes.def: Reduced density of hairs.

nodes.label: Short distal phalanx of finger
nodes.def: Short distance from the end of the finger to the most distal interphalangeal crease or the distal interphalangeal joint flexion point. That is, hypoplasia of one or more of the distal phalanx of finger.

nodes.label: Duplication of the distal phalanx of hand
nodes.def: This term applies if one or more of the distal phalanges of the hand are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

nodes.label: Complete duplication of phalanx of hand
nodes.def: A complete duplication affecting one or more of the phalanges of the hand. As opposed to a partial duplication were there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones, a complete duplication leads to two separate bones appearing side to side (radio-ulnar axis) as seen on x-rays. A duplication leading to an accessory bone appearing in the proximo-distal axis on x-rays, is a different entity called a Pseudoepiphyses (see according terms) sometimes also referred to as Hyperphalangism.

nodes.label: Partial duplication of the phalanx of hand
nodes.def: A partial duplication, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance, affecting one or more of the phalanges of the hand. As opposed to a complete duplication there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones.

nodes.label: Bullet-shaped toe phalanx
nodes.def: An abnormal morphology of one or more phalanges of the toes, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

nodes.label: Curved toe phalanx
nodes.def: A deviation from the normal straight form of one or more toe phalanges.

nodes.label: Triangular shaped phalanges of the toes
Abnormal fetal cardiovascular morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the fetal circulation system. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

nodes.label: Abnormal glucose homeostasis
nodes.def: Abnormality of glucose homeostasis.

nodes.label: Internal hemorrhage
nodes.def: The presence of hemorrhage within the body.

nodes.label: Abnormal intrahepatic bile duct morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the intrahepatic bile duct.

nodes.label: Abnormality of dental structure
nodes.def: An abnormality of the structure or composition of the teeth.

nodes.label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the metacarpal bones
nodes.def: Aplasia or Hypoplasia affecting the metacarpal bones.

nodes.label: Abnormal atrioventricular connection
nodes.def: An abnormality of the circulatory connection between atria and ventricles.

nodes.label: Hepatitis
nodes.def: Inflammation of the liver.

nodes.label: Abnormal erythroid lineage cell morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of erythroid lineage cells, that is, of the erythropoietic cells in the lineage leading to and including erythrocytes.

nodes.label: Abnormal fourth toe morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the fourth toe.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the palmar creases
nodes.def: An abnormality of the creases of the skin of palm of hand.

nodes.label: Enlarged epiphyses
nodes.def: Increased size of epiphyses.

nodes.label: Abnormal curvature of the vertebral column
nodes.def: The presence of an abnormal curvature of the vertebral column.

nodes.label: Abnormal sperm tail morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the sperm tail.

nodes.label: Infection following live vaccination
nodes.def: An infection resulting from live attenuated vaccines (LAV), that is, a vaccine prepared from living viruses or bacteria that have been weakened under laboratory conditions. LAV vaccines will replicate in a vaccinated individual and produce an immune response but usually cause mild or no disease. are derived from disease-causing pathogens.

nodes.label: Abnormal lymph-node follicle architecture
nodes.def: Any phenotypic abnormality of the architecture of follicles of a lymph node.

nodes.label: Abnormal hippocampus morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the hippocampus,

nodes.label: Abnormal liver parenchyma morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the liver located predominantly in the hepatocytes as opposed to stromal cells.

nodes.label: Arrhythmia
nodes.def: Any cardiac rhythm other than the normal sinus rhythm. Such a rhythm may be either of sinus or ectopic origin and either regular or irregular. An arrhythmia may be due to a disturbance in impulse formation or conduction or both.

nodes.label: Abnormal response to endocrine stimulation test
nodes.def: An anomalous response to a test that is designed to probe the function of the endocrine system.

nodes.label: Abnormal periosteum morphology
nodes.def: An anomalous structure of the periosteum, i.e., of the membrane that covers the outer surface of bones.

nodes.label: Soft tissue sarcoma
nodes.def: A type of sarcoma (A connective tissue neoplasm formed by proliferation of mesodermal cells) that develops from soft tissues like fat, muscle, nerves, fibrous tissues, blood vessels, or deep skin tissues.

nodes.label: Medial degeneration
nodes.def: Medial degeneration of the aorta is to be used as an overarching term for any aortic surgical specimens that demonstrate one or more of the specific histopathologies mucoid extracellular matrix accumulation, elastic fiber fragmentation and/or loss, elastic fiber thinning, elastic fiber disorganization, smooth muscle cell nuclei loss, laminar medial collapse, smooth muscle cell disorganization, medial fibrosis. Grading of medial degeneration is based on the average overall severity of specific histopathologies as described, considering the worst area(s) sampled from multiple slides and aorta sections.

nodes.label: Abnormal peripheral nervous system physiology
nodes.def: Any functional abnormality of the part of the nervous system that consists of the nerves and ganglia outside of the brain and spinal cord.

nodes.label: Severe infection
nodes.def: A type of infection that is regarded as a sign of a pathological susceptibility to infection because of unusual severity or intensity of the infection.

nodes.label: Opportunistic bacterial infection
nodes.def: An infection that is caused by a bacterium that would generally not be able to cause an infection in a host with a normal immune system. Such bacteria take advantage of the opportunity, so to speak, that is provided by a weakened immune system.

nodes.label: Neoplasm by histology
nodes.def: Neoplasm categorized according to type of histological abnormality.

nodes.label: Abnormal T cell physiology
nodes.def: A functional anomaly of T cells.

nodes.label: Abnormal musculoskeletal physiology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the function of the skeletal system.

nodes.label: Abnormal iliac wing morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the ilium ala. This is the large expanded portion of the ilum which bounds the greater pelvis laterally.

nodes.label: Focal aware emotional seizure
nodes.def: A focal emotional seizure during which awareness is retained throughout the seizure.

nodes.label: Focal impaired awareness emotional seizure
nodes.def: A focal emotional seizure in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

nodes.label: Abnormal glomerular capillary lumen morphology
nodes.def: Abnormal structural characteristics of the interior space of the capillary of the renal glomerulus.

nodes.label: Abnormal interlobular vein intima/media morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the inner or middle layer of the interlobular veins of the kidney.

nodes.label: Abnormal fetal physiology
nodes.def: Any functional anomaly of the fetus.

nodes.label: Anti-aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase antibody positivity
nodes.def: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against a tRNA synthetase enzyme.

nodes.label: Neurofibroma by anatomical location
nodes.def: Neurofibroma categorized according to the anatomical site of origin.

nodes.label: Abnormal leukocyte enzyme concentration or activity
nodes.def: Concentration or activity of an enzyme as measured in leukocytes is above or below the limits of normal.

nodes.label: Abnormal anus morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the anus.

nodes.label: Focal non-motor seizure
nodes.def: A type of focal-onset seizure characterized by non-motor signs or symptoms (or behavior arrest) as its initial semiological manifestation.

nodes.label: Synostosis involving bones of the toes
Synostosis of joints
nodes.def: The abnormal fusion of neighboring bones across a joint.

nodes.label: Abnormal tendon morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the structure or form of the tendons, also often called sinews.

nodes.label: Cerebral inclusion bodies
nodes.def: Nuclear or cytoplasmic aggregates of stainable substances within cells of the brain.

nodes.label: Sclerosis of distal phalanx of finger
nodes.def: An elevation in bone density in one or more distal phalanges of the fingers. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

nodes.label: Sclerosis of middle phalanx of finger
nodes.def: An elevation in bone density in one or more middle phalanges of the fingers. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

nodes.label: Sclerosis of proximal phalanx of finger
nodes.def: An elevation in bone density in one or more proximal phalanges of the fingers. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

nodes.label: Skin nodule
nodes.def: Morphologically similar to a papule, but greater than either 10mm in both width and depth, and most frequently centered in the dermis or subcutaneous fat.

nodes.label: Fractured phalanx
nodes.def: A partial or complete breakage of the phalanx.

nodes.label: Abnormal head blood vessel morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of a blood vessel of the head, including branches of the arterial and venous systems of the head.

nodes.label: Sensory seeking
nodes.def: Unusual interest in sensory aspects of the environment.

nodes.label: Recurrent maladaptive behavior
nodes.def: A repeating behavior that is either immediately unproductive or has negative long-term consequences. This includes harmful coping mechanisms such as addictive behavior and failure to control impulses and compulsions.

nodes.label: Severe viral infection
nodes.def: An unusually severe viral infection.

nodes.label: Abnormal oral physiology
nodes.def: A functional anomaly of the mouth (which is also known as the oral cavity).

nodes.label: Abnormal cortical radial artery intima/media morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the inner or middle layer of the cortical radial arteries (also known as interlobular arteries) of the kidney.

nodes.label: Neoplasm of the endocrine system
nodes.def: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the endocrine system.

nodes.label: Rectal fistula
nodes.def: The presence of a fistula affecting the rectum.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the lymphatic system
nodes.def: An anomaly of the lymphatic system, a network of lymphatic vessels that carry a clear fluid called lymph unidirectionally towards either the right lymphatic duct or the thoracic duct, which in turn drain into the right and left subclavian veins respectively.

nodes.label: Abnormal uvula morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the uvula, the conic projection from the posterior edge of the middle of the soft palate.

nodes.label: Abnormal upper lip morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the upper lip.

nodes.label: Abnormal lower lip morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the lower lip.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the middle ear
nodes.def: An abnormality of the middle ear.

nodes.label: Retinal dystrophy
nodes.def: Retinal dystrophy is an abnormality of the retina associated with a hereditary process. Retinal dystrophies are defined by their predominantly monogenic inheritance and they are frequently associated with loss or dysfunction of photoreceptor cells as a primary or secondary event.

nodes.label: Retinal hemorrhage
nodes.def: Hemorrhage occurring within the retina.

nodes.label: Scotoma
nodes.def: A regional and pathological increase of the light detection threshold in any region of the visual field surrounded by a field of normal or relatively well-preserved vision.

nodes.label: Abnormal pupil morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the pupil.

nodes.label: Disinhibition
nodes.def: Reduced ability to control, or a failure to resist a temptation, urge, or impulse. Examples include disregard for social conventions, general impulsivity, and poor risk assessment.

nodes.label: Hallucinations
nodes.def: Perceptions in a conscious and awake state that, in the absence of external stimuli, have qualities of real perception. These perceptions are vivid, substantial, and located in external objective space.

nodes.label: Abnormal thymus morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the thymus, an organ located in the upper anterior portion of the chest cavity just behind the sternum and whose main function is to provide an environment for T lymphocyte maturation.

nodes.label: Abnormal external genitalia morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the external genitalia.

nodes.label: Pruritus
nodes.def: Pruritus is an itch or a sensation that makes a person want to scratch. This term refers to an abnormally increased disposition to experience pruritus.

nodes.label: Xanthomatosis
nodes.def: The presence of multiple xanthomas (xanthomata) in the skin. Xanthomas are yellowish, firm, lipid-laden nodules in the skin.

nodes.label: Telangiectasia
nodes.def: Telangiectasias refer to small dilated blood vessels located near the surface of the skin or mucous membranes, measuring between 0.5 and 1 millimeter in diameter. Telangiectasia are located especially on the tongue, lips, palate, fingers, face, conjunctiva, trunk, nail beds, and fingertips.

nodes.label: Pterygium
nodes.def: Pterygia are 'winglike' triangular membranes occurring in the neck, eyes, knees, elbows, ankles or digits.

nodes.label: Abnormal morphology of the nasal alae
nodes.def: An abnormality of the Ala of nose.

nodes.label: Abnormal pericardium morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the pericardium, i.e., of the fluid filled sac that surrounds the heart and the proximal ends of the aorta, vena cava, and the pulmonary artery.

nodes.label: Foot polydactyly
nodes.def: A kind of polydactyly characterized by the presence of a supernumerary toe or toes.

nodes.label: Acidosis
nodes.def: Abnormal acid accumulation or depletion of base.

nodes.label: Metabolic acidosis
nodes.def: Metabolic acidosis (MA) is characterized by a fall in blood pH due to a reduction of serum bicarbonate concentration. This can occur as a result of either the accumulation of acids (high anion gap MA) or the loss of bicarbonate from the gastrointestinal tract or the kidney (hyperchloremic MA). By definition, MA is not due to a respirary cause.

nodes.label: Abnormal glomerular mesangium morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the mesangium, i.e., of the central part of the renal glomerulus between capillaries.

nodes.label: Organic aciduria
nodes.def: Excretion of non-amino organic acids in urine.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the abdominal organs
nodes.def: An abnormality of the viscera of the abdomen.

nodes.label: Dysphagia
nodes.def: Difficulty in swallowing.

nodes.label: Abnormality of extrapyramidal motor function
nodes.def: A neurological condition related to lesions of the basal ganglia leading to typical abnormalities including akinesia (inability to initiate changes in activity and perform volitional movements rapidly and easily), muscular rigidity (continuous contraction of muscles with constant resistance to passive movement), chorea (widespread arrhythmic movements of a forcible, rapid, jerky, and restless nature), athetosis (inability to sustain the muscles of the fingers, toes, or other group of muscles in a fixed position), and akathisia (inability to remain motionless).

nodes.label: Encephalocele
nodes.def: A neural tube defect characterized by sac-like protrusions of the brain and the membranes that cover it through openings in the skull.

nodes.label: Ventriculomegaly
nodes.def: An increase in size of the ventricular system of the brain.

nodes.label: Apraxia
nodes.def: A defect in the understanding of complex motor commands and in the execution of certain learned movements, i.e., deficits in the cognitive components of learned movements.

nodes.label: Headache
nodes.def: Cephalgia, or pain sensed in various parts of the head, not confined to the area of distribution of any nerve.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the hand
nodes.def: An abnormality affecting one or both hands.

nodes.label: Brachydactyly
nodes.def: Digits that appear disproportionately short compared to the hand/foot. The word brachydactyly is used here to describe a series distinct patterns of shortened digits (brachydactyly types A-E). This is the sense used here.

nodes.label: Abnormal fingernail morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the fingernails.

nodes.label: Intellectual disability
nodes.def: Intellectual disability, previously referred to as mental retardation, is characterized by subnormal intellectual functioning that occurs during the developmental period. It is defined by an IQ score below 70.

nodes.label: Cerebellar atrophy
nodes.def: Cerebellar atrophy is defined as a cerebellum with initially normal structures, in a posterior fossa with normal size, which displays enlarged fissures (interfolial spaces) in comparison to the foliae secondary to loss of tissue. Cerebellar atrophy implies irreversible loss of tissue and result from an ongoing progressive disease until a final stage is reached or a single injury, e.g. an intoxication or infectious event.

nodes.label: Abnormal corpus callosum morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the corpus callosum.

nodes.label: Craniosynostosis
nodes.def: Craniosynostosis refers to the premature closure of the cranial sutures. Primary craniosynostosis refers to the closure of one or more sutures due to abnormalities in skull development, and secondary craniosynostosis results from failure of brain growth.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the musculature of the hand
Abnormality of the musculature of the lower limbs
Abnormal umbilicus morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the structure or appearance of the umbilicus.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the amniotic fluid
nodes.def: Abnormality of the amniotic fluid, which is the fluid contained in the amniotic sac surrounding the developing fetus.

nodes.label: Ventricular septal defect
nodes.def: A hole between the two bottom chambers (ventricles) of the heart. The defect is centered around the most superior aspect of the ventricular septum.

nodes.label: Atrial septal defect
nodes.def: Atrial septal defect (ASD) is a congenital abnormality of the interatrial septum that enables blood flow between the left and right atria via the interatrial septum.

nodes.label: Hernia of the abdominal wall
nodes.def: The presence of a hernia in the abdominal wall.

nodes.label: Abnormal macrophage morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of macrophages.

nodes.label: Reduced bone mineral density
nodes.def: A reduction of bone mineral density, that is, of the amount of matter per cubic centimeter of bones.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating pyrimidine concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a pyrimidine in the blood circulation.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating fatty-acid concentration
nodes.def: A deviation from the normal concentration of a fatty acid in the blood circulation.

nodes.label: Abnormality of temperature regulation
nodes.def: An abnormality of temperature homeostasis.

nodes.label: Recurrent viral infections
nodes.def: Increased susceptibility to viral infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of viral infection.

nodes.label: Ventricular tachycardia
nodes.def: A tachycardia originating in the ventricles characterized by rapid heart rate (over 100 beats per minute) and broad QRS complexes (over 120 ms).

nodes.label: Recurrent fungal infections
nodes.def: Increased susceptibility to fungal infections, as manifested by multiple episodes of fungal infection.

nodes.label: Autoimmunity
nodes.def: The occurrence of an immune reaction against the organism's own cells or tissues.

nodes.label: Abnormal forearm morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the lower arm.

nodes.label: Dislocated radial head
nodes.def: A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint.

nodes.label: Lactic acidosis
nodes.def: An abnormal buildup of lactic acid in the body, leading to acidification of the blood and other bodily fluids.

nodes.label: Abnormal hip bone morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the hip bone.

nodes.label: Abnormal nostril morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the nostril.

nodes.label: Lower-limb joint contracture
nodes.def: A limitation in the passive range of motion of a joint of the lower limb resulting from loss of elasticity in the periarticular tissues owing to structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules or skin.

nodes.label: Metacarpophalangeal synostosis
nodes.def: Fusion of a metacarpal bone with the proximal phalanx of the finger distal to it across the corresponding metacarpophalangeal joint.

nodes.label: Arterial tortuosity
nodes.def: Abnormal tortuous (i.e., twisted) form of arteries.

nodes.label: Proximal symphalangism of hands
nodes.def: The term proximal symphalangism refers to a bony fusion of the middle and proximal phalanges of the digits of the hand, in other words the proximal interphalangeal joint (PIJ) is missing which can be seen either on x-rays or as an absence of the proximal interphalangeal finger creases.

nodes.label: Abnormality of primary teeth
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the primary tooth.

nodes.label: Focal-onset seizure
nodes.def: A focal-onset seizure is a type of seizure originating within networks limited to one hemisphere. They may be discretely localized or more widely distributed, and may originate in subcortical structures.

nodes.label: Abnormal cerebellar vermis morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the vermis of cerebellum.

nodes.label: EEG abnormality
nodes.def: Abnormality observed by electroencephalogram (EEG), which is used to record of the brain's spontaneous electrical activity from multiple electrodes placed on the scalp.

nodes.label: Acute leukemia
nodes.def: A clonal (malignant) hematopoietic disorder with an acute onset, affecting the bone marrow and the peripheral blood. The malignant cells show minimal differentiation and are called blasts, either myeloid blasts (myeloblasts) or lymphoid blasts (lymphoblasts).

nodes.label: Abnormal peritoneum morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the peritoneum.

nodes.label: Vascular dilatation
nodes.def: Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the wall of an artery, vein or the heart.

nodes.label: Abnormal skull base morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the base of the skull, which forms the floor of the cranial cavity and separates the brain from other facial structures. The skull base is made up of five bones: the ethmoid, sphenoid, occipital, paired frontal, and paired parietal bones, and is subdivided into 3 regions: the anterior, middle, and posterior cranial fossae. The petro-occipital fissure subdivides the middle cranial fossa into 1 central component and 2 lateral components.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the calcaneus
nodes.def: An abnormality of the calcaneus, also known as the heel bone, one of the or heel bone, one of the components of the tarsus of the foot which make up the heel.

nodes.label: Tarsal synostosis
nodes.def: Synostosis (bony fusion) involving one or more bones of the tarsus (calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, cuneiiform bones).

nodes.label: Vertebral hypoplasia
nodes.def: Small, underdeveloped vertebral bodies.

nodes.label: Abnormal ossification involving the femoral head and neck
Carpal synostosis
nodes.def: Synostosis (bony fusion) involving one or more bones of the carpus (scaphoid, lunate, triquetrum, trapezium, trapezoid, capitate, hamate, pisiform).

nodes.label: Aplasia/hypoplasia of the extremities
nodes.def: Absence (due to failure to form) or underdevelopment of the extremities.

nodes.label: Ocular anterior segment dysgenesis
nodes.def: Abnormal development (dysgenesis) of the anterior segment of the eye globe. These structures are mainly of mesenchymal origin.

nodes.label: Abnormal iris pigmentation
nodes.def: Abnormal pigmentation of the iris.

nodes.label: Aplasia of the distal phalanges of the hand
Duplication of the proximal phalanx of hand
nodes.def: This term applies if one or more of the proximal phalanges of the hand are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

nodes.label: Aplasia of the middle phalanx of the hand
nodes.def: Absence of one or more middle phalanx of a finger.

nodes.label: Short proximal phalanx of finger
nodes.def: Congenital hypoplasia of one or more proximal phalanx of finger.

nodes.label: Aplasia of the proximal phalanges of the hand
Ivory epiphyses of the distal phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Distal epiphyses of the hand are hard and dense like ivory. Such an epiphysis has a uniformly dense appearance on radiographs.

nodes.label: Fragmentation of the epiphyses of the middle phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Fragmented appearance of the epiphyses of the middle phalanges of the hand.

nodes.label: Ivory epiphyses of the middle phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Epiphyses of the middle phalanges of the hand are hard and dense like ivory. Such an epiphysis has a uniformly dense appearance on radiographs.

nodes.label: Ivory epiphyses of the proximal phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Epiphyses of the proximal phalanges of the hand are hard and dense like ivory. Such an epiphysis has a uniformly dense appearance on radiographs.

nodes.label: Abnormal spinal meningeal morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the spinal meninges, the system of membranes (dura mater, the arachnoid mater, and the pia mater) which envelops the spinal cord.

nodes.label: Abnormal prostate morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the prostate.

nodes.label: Uterine neoplasm
nodes.def: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the uterus.

nodes.label: Zonular cataract
nodes.def: Zonular cataracts are defined to be cataracts that affect specific regions of the lens.

nodes.label: Anemia of inadequate production
nodes.def: A kind of anemia characterized by inadequate production of erythrocytes.

nodes.label: Abnormal morphology of the musculature of the neck
nodes.def: An abnormality of the neck musculature.

nodes.label: Abnormal fallopian tube morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the fallopian tube.

nodes.label: Aplasia/hypoplasia involving bones of the hand
nodes.def: Absence (due to failure to form) or underdevelopment of the bones of the hand.

nodes.label: EEG with generalized epileptiform discharges
nodes.def: EEG discharges recorded on the entire scalp typically seen in persons with epilepsy.

nodes.label: Abnormal fontanelle morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the fontanelle.

nodes.label: Abnormality of mouth shape
nodes.def: An abnormality of the outline, configuration, or contour of the mouth.

nodes.label: Abnormality of upper lip vermillion
nodes.def: An abnormality of the vermilion border, the sharp demarcation between the lip (red colored) and the adjacent normal skin.

nodes.label: Abnormal semicircular canal morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the morphology of the semicircular canal.

nodes.label: Abnormal CNS myelination
nodes.def: An abnormality of myelination of nerves in the central nervous system.

nodes.label: Abnormal maternal serum screening
nodes.def: An abnormally elevated or decreased level of a maternal serum marker analytes used in screening for aneuploidy.

nodes.label: Abnormal corneal epithelium morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the corneal epithelium, that is of the epithelial tissue that covers the front of the cornea.

nodes.label: Abnormal spatial orientation of the cardiac segments
nodes.def: Abnormality of the spatial relationship of the cardiac segments to other components of the heart.

nodes.label: Congenital malformation of the great arteries
nodes.def: Defect or defects of the morphogenesis of the aorta and pulmonary arteries.

nodes.label: Congenital defect of the pericardium
nodes.def: A developmental defect of the pericardium with congenital onset.

nodes.label: Abnormal coronary artery origin
nodes.def: Isolated abnormalities of the coronary artery origins. This may be in associated with other structural heart malformations but not the patterns of complex structural heart malformations which result in abnormal course of the coronary arteries.

nodes.label: Lipoma
nodes.def: Benign neoplasia derived from lipoblasts or lipocytes of white or brown fat. May be angiomatous or hibernomatous.

nodes.label: Abnormal second toe morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the second toe.

nodes.label: Abnormal third toe morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the third toe.

nodes.label: Abnormal fifth toe morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the little toe.

nodes.label: Facial palsy
nodes.def: Facial nerve palsy is a dysfunction of cranial nerve VII (the facial nerve) that results in inability to control facial muscles on the affected side with weakness of the muscles of facial expression and eye closure. This can either be present in unilateral or bilateral form.

nodes.label: Abnormal epiphyseal ossification
nodes.def: An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of an epiphysis.

nodes.label: Abnormality of hair texture
nodes.def: An abnormality of the texture of the hair.

nodes.label: Decreased circulating level of specific antibody
nodes.def: The presence of normal overall immunoglobulin levels with deficiency of specific immunoglobulins directed against a specific antigen or microorganism.

nodes.label: Abnormal labia majora morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the outer labia.

nodes.label: Abnormal urine protein level
nodes.def: Any deviation of the concentration of one or more proteins in the urine.

nodes.label: Motor seizure
nodes.def: A motor seizure is a type of seizure that is characterized at onset by involvement of the skeletal musculature. The motor event could consist of an increase (positive) or decrease (negative) in muscle contraction to produce a movement.

nodes.label: Abnormal lymph-node tissue architecture
nodes.def: Any phenotypic abnormality of the architecture of the tissue of a lymph node.

nodes.label: Abnormal glomerular capillary morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the capillary blood vessels in the renal glomerulus.

nodes.label: Abnormality of skin adnexa physiology
nodes.def: Any functional anomaly of the skin adnexa (skin appendages), which are specialized skin structures located within the dermis and focally within the subcutaneous fatty tissue, comprising three histologically distinct structures: (1) the pilosebaceous unit (hair follicle and sebaceous glands); (2) the eccrine sweat glands; and (3) the apocrine glands.

nodes.label: Broad distal phalanx of finger
nodes.def: Abnormally wide (broad) distal phalanx of finger.

nodes.label: Broad proximal phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Increased width of the proximal phalanges of the finger.

nodes.label: Fetal neck anomaly
nodes.def: A structural anomaly in the fetal neck region. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

nodes.label: Neuroepithelial neoplasm
nodes.def: A neoplasm composed of neural epithelium, not necessarily a neoplasm located in the neural epithelium or neuroepithelium.

nodes.label: Abnormal retinal morphology on macular OCT
Abnormal foveal morphology on macular OCT
Abnormal jaw morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the jaw, the bony structure of the mouth that consists of the mandible and the maxilla.

nodes.label: Abnormal breath sound
nodes.def: An anomalous (adventitious) sound produced by the breathing process.

nodes.label: Abnormal rib ossification
nodes.def: An anomaly of the process of rib bone formation.

nodes.label: Abnormal autonomic nervous system physiology
nodes.def: A functional abnormality of the autonomic nervous system.

nodes.label: Abnormal protein N-linked glycosylation
nodes.def: An anomaly of protein N-linked glycosylation, i.e., an abnormality of the protein glycosylation process in which a carbohydrate or carbohydrate derivative unit is added to a protein via a nitrogen atom in an amino acid residue in a protein.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating thyroid hormone concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal range of the hormones produced by the thyroid gland.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating androgen level
nodes.def: An anomaly in the blood concentration of an androgen, that is, of a steroid hormone that controls development and maintenance of masculine characteristics. The androgens include testosterone and Dehydroepiandrosterone.

nodes.label: Eyelid laxity
nodes.def: Abnormally lax eyelid associated with tissue relaxation; it can be demonstrated by the eyelid distraction test and/or the eyelid snap test.

nodes.label: Joint subluxation
nodes.def: A partial dislocation of a joint.

nodes.label: Abnormal involuntary eye movements
nodes.def: Anomalous movements of the eyes that occur without the subject wanting them to happen.

nodes.label: Abnormal urinary electrolyte concentration
nodes.def: An abnormality in the concentration of electrolytes in the urine.

nodes.label: Abnormal nervous system morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the nervous system.

nodes.label: Abnormal neuron morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of a neuron. Neurons are electrically excitable cells that transmit signals throughout the body. Neurons employ both electrical and chemical components in the transmission of information. Neurons are connected to other neurons at synapses and connected to effector organs or cells at neuroeffector junctions.

nodes.label: Abnormal granulocyte count
nodes.def: Abnormal increase or decrease of absolute number of granulocytes in the blood, per microliter, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the anterior pituitary
nodes.def: An abnormality of the adenohypophysis, which is also known as the anterior lobe of the pituitary gland.

nodes.label: Abnormal platelet morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly in platelet form, ultrastructure, or intracellular organelles.

nodes.label: Abnormal platelet membrane protein expression
nodes.def: Presence of reduced amount of a membrane protein on the cell membrane of platelets. This feature is typically measured by flow cytometry.

nodes.label: Abnormal leukocyte count
nodes.def: Number of leukocytes per volume of blood beyond normal limits.

nodes.label: Abnormal neutrophil physiology
nodes.def: Any functional abnormality of neutrophils.

nodes.label: Abnormal CD4+ T cell subset proportion
nodes.def: Abnormal increase or decrease of helper CD3+CD4+ T cells, measured as percentage of total CD3+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group. These are usually measured within the TCR alpha/beta positive population.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating proteinogenic amino acid concentration
nodes.def: An elevated level of a proteinogenic amino acid in the blood circulation. These are the 23 alpha-amino acids that are precursors to proteins, and are incorporated into proteins during translation. The group includes the 20 amino acids encoded by the nuclear genes of eukaryotes together with selenocysteine, pyrrolysine, and N-formylmethionine.

nodes.label: Abnormal right ventricular function
nodes.def: Anomalous physiology (function) of the right ventricle.

nodes.label: Low 10-minute APGAR score
nodes.def: A normal APGAR score can be coded as 'not Low 10-minute APGAR score'.

nodes.label: Open neural tube defect
nodes.def: A type of neural tube defect that is not covered by skin.

nodes.label: Gastrointestinal ulcer
nodes.def: A deep defect in the esophageal, gastric, duodenal or intestinal wall involving the entire mucosal thickness and penetrating through the muscularis mucosae.

nodes.label: Mendelian inheritance
nodes.def: A mode of inheritance of diseases whose pathophysiology can be traced back to deleterious variants in a single gene. The inheritance patterns of these single-gene (monogenic) diseases are often referred to as Mendelian in honor of Gregor Mendel.

nodes.label: Vasculitis by anatomical site
nodes.def: Vasculitis categorized according to the anatomical site where the finding is localized.

nodes.label: Elevated circulating medium-chain acylcarnitine concentration
nodes.def: Concentration of medium-chain acylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Acylcarnitines are classified according to the number of carbon atoms in the acyl-chain. Medium-chain acylcarnitines have between six and twelve carbon atoms in the acyl-chain (C6-C12),

nodes.label: Scaling skin
nodes.def: Refers to the loss of the outer layer of the epidermis in large, scale-like flakes.

nodes.label: Neoplasm of the peripheral nervous system
nodes.def: A benign or malignant neoplasm (tumor) of the peripheral nervous system.

nodes.label: Intestinal atresia
nodes.def: An abnormal closure, or atresia of the tubular structure of the intestine.

nodes.label: Benign neoplasm of the central nervous system
Sclerosis of middle phalanx of toe
nodes.def: An elevation in bone density in one or more middle phalanges of the toes. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

nodes.label: Sclerosis of distal phalanx of toe
nodes.def: An elevation in bone density in one or more distal phalanges of the toes. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

nodes.label: Abnormal substantia nigra morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the substantia nigra, which is a midbrain dopaminergic nucleus which has a critical role in modulating motor movement and reward functions as part of the basal ganglia circuitry.

nodes.label: Positive skin infectious agent test
nodes.def: Any kind of test for an infectious agent in skin positive.

nodes.label: Abnormal lung development
nodes.def: A structural defect associated with abnormal development of the lung.

nodes.label: Increased anti-food allergen IgE antibody level
nodes.def: Increased level of IgE antibody against proteins found in foods, such as milk, egg, soy, wheat, peanut, treenut, fish, and shellfish.

nodes.label: Abnormal heart sound
nodes.def: Any abnormal noise generated by the beating heart.

nodes.label: Abnormal oral morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the mouth, which is also known as the oral cavity.

nodes.label: Anti-histone antibody positivity
nodes.def: The presence of autoantibodies in the blood circulation that react against histone antigens.

nodes.label: Abnormal exteroceptive sensation
nodes.def: A type of somatic sensory dysfunction characterized by abnormality of superficial sensation that is mediated by receptors in skin and mucous membranes.

nodes.label: Neoplasm of the heart
nodes.def: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the heart.

nodes.label: Abnormal forebrain morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the forebrain, which has as its parts the telencephalon, diencephalon, lateral ventricles and third ventricle.

nodes.label: Neoplasm of the oral cavity
nodes.def: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the oral cavity.

nodes.label: Self-injurious behavior
nodes.def: Self-aggression.

nodes.label: Abnormal lymphatic vessel morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the vessel that contains or conveys lymph fluid.

nodes.label: Exostoses
nodes.def: An exostosis is a benign growth the projects outward from the bone surface. It is capped by cartilage, and arises from a bone that develops from cartilage.

nodes.label: Abnormal male internal genitalia morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the male internal genitalia.

nodes.label: Proteinuria
nodes.def: Increased levels of protein in the urine.

nodes.label: Glomerulonephritis
nodes.def: Inflammation of the renal glomeruli.

nodes.label: Nephrotic syndrome
nodes.def: Nephrotic syndrome is a collection of findings resulting from glomerular dysfunction with an increase in glomerular capillary wall permeability associated with pronounced proteinuria. Nephrotic syndrome refers to the constellation of clinical findings that result from severe renal loss of protein, with Proteinuria and hypoalbuminemia, edema, and hyperlipidemia.

nodes.label: Ovarian cyst
nodes.def: The presence of one or more cysts of the ovary.

nodes.label: Cleft palate
nodes.def: Cleft palate is a developmental defect of the palate resulting from a failure of fusion of the palatine processes and manifesting as a separation of the roof of the mouth (soft and hard palate).

nodes.label: Abnormal parotid gland morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the parotid glands, which are the salivary glands that are located in the subcutaneous tissues of the face overlying the mandibular ramus and anterior and inferior to the external ear.

nodes.label: Cleft upper lip
nodes.def: A gap or groove in the upper lip. This is a congenital defect resulting from nonfusion of tissues of the lip during embryonal development.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the head
nodes.def: An abnormality of the head.

nodes.label: Abnormal anterior fontanelle morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the anterior fontanelle, i.e., the cranial fontanelle that is located at the intersection of the coronal and sagittal sutures.

nodes.label: Abnormal location of ears
nodes.def: Abnormal location of the ear.

nodes.label: Uveitis
nodes.def: Inflammation of one or all portions of the uveal tract.

nodes.label: Esotropia
nodes.def: A form of strabismus with one or both eyes turned inward ('crossed') to a relatively severe degree, usually defined as 10 diopters or more.

nodes.label: Abnormal saccadic eye movements
nodes.def: An abnormality of eye movement characterized by impairment of fast (saccadic) eye movements.

nodes.label: Coloboma
nodes.def: A developmental defect characterized by a cleft of some portion of the eye or ocular adnexa.

nodes.label: Ophthalmoplegia
nodes.def: Paralysis of one or more extraocular muscles that are responsible for eye movements.

nodes.label: Abnormal nasolacrimal system morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the nasolacrimal drainage system, which serves as a conduit for tear flow from the external eye to the nasal cavity.

nodes.label: Lacrimation abnormality
nodes.def: Abnormality of tear production.

nodes.label: Horizontal nystagmus
nodes.def: Nystagmus consisting of horizontal to-and-fro eye movements.

nodes.label: Peripheral axonal degeneration
nodes.def: Progressive deterioration of peripheral axons.

nodes.label: Congenital diaphragmatic hernia
nodes.def: The presence of a hernia of the diaphragm present at birth.

nodes.label: Nephrolithiasis
nodes.def: The presence of calculi (stones) in the kidneys.

nodes.label: Diabetes mellitus
nodes.def: A group of abnormalities characterized by hyperglycemia and glucose intolerance.

nodes.label: Hypertension
nodes.def: The presence of chronic increased pressure in the systemic arterial system.

nodes.label: Precocious puberty
nodes.def: The onset of secondary sexual characteristics before a normal age. Although it is difficult to define normal age ranges because of the marked variation with which puberty begins in normal children, precocious puberty can be defined as the onset of puberty before the age of 8 years in girls or 9 years in boys.

nodes.label: Anterior hypopituitarism
nodes.def: A condition of reduced function of the anterior pituitary gland characterized by decreased secretion of one or more of the pituitary hormones growth hormone, thyroid-stimulating hormone, adrenocorticotropic hormone, prolactin, luteinizing hormone, and follicle-stimulating hormone.

nodes.label: Eczematoid dermatitis
nodes.def: Eczema is a form of dermatitis that is characterized by scaly, pruritic, erythematous lesions located on flexural surfaces.

nodes.label: Hypermelanotic macule
nodes.def: A hyperpigmented circumscribed area of change in normal skin color without elevation or depression of any size.

nodes.label: Neurofibroma
nodes.def: A benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor that generally appears as a soft, skin-colored papule or small subcutaneous nodule. Individuals with neurofibromatosis can have numerous neurofibromas.

nodes.label: Otitis media
nodes.def: Inflammation or infection of the middle ear.

nodes.label: Conjunctivitis
nodes.def: Inflammation of the conjunctiva.

nodes.label: Atrial arrhythmia
nodes.def: A type of supraventricular tachycardia in which the atria are the principal site of electrophysiologic disturbance.

nodes.label: Abnormal vestibular function
nodes.def: An abnormality of the functioning of the vestibular apparatus.

nodes.label: Toe clinodactyly
nodes.def: Bending or curvature of a toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe).

nodes.label: Anemia
nodes.def: A reduction in erythrocytes volume or hemoglobin concentration.

nodes.label: Leukemia
nodes.def: A cancer of the blood and bone marrow characterized by an abnormal proliferation of leukocytes.

nodes.label: Abnormality of coagulation
nodes.def: An abnormality of the process of blood coagulation. That is, altered ability or inability of the blood to clot.

nodes.label: Abnormal scalp morphology
nodes.def: Any anomaly of the scalp, the skin an subcutaneous tissue of the head on which head hair grows.

nodes.label: Cerebral cortical atrophy
nodes.def: Atrophy of the cortex of the cerebrum.

nodes.label: Generalized non-motor (absence) seizure
nodes.def: A generalized non-motor (absence) seizure is a type of a type of dialeptic seizure that is of electrographically generalized onset. It is a generalized seizure characterized by an interruption of activities, a blank stare, and usually the person will be unresponsive when spoken to. Any ictal motor phenomena are minor in comparison to these non-motor features.

nodes.label: Polymicrogyria
nodes.def: Polymicrogyria is a congenital malformation of the cerebral cortex characterized by abnormal cortical layering (lamination) and an excessive number of small gyri (folds).

nodes.label: Gliosis
nodes.def: Gliosis is the focal proliferation of glial cells in the central nervous system.

nodes.label: Delayed gross motor development
nodes.def: A type of motor delay characterized by a delay in acquiring the ability to control the large muscles of the body for walking, running, sitting, and crawling.

nodes.label: Gastrointestinal hemorrhage
nodes.def: Hemorrhage affecting the gastrointestinal tract.

nodes.label: Hand polydactyly
nodes.def: A kind of polydactyly characterized by the presence of a supernumerary finger or fingers.

nodes.label: Joint dislocation
nodes.def: Displacement or malalignment of joints.

nodes.label: Abnormal pulmonary valve morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the pulmonary valve.

nodes.label: Recurrent upper respiratory tract infections
nodes.def: An increased susceptibility to upper respiratory tract infections as manifested by a history of recurrent upper respiratory tract infections (running ears - otitis, sinusitis, pharyngitis, tonsillitis).

nodes.label: Osteolysis
nodes.def: Osteolysis refers to the destruction of bone through bone resorption with removal or loss of calcium.

nodes.label: Abnormal 2nd finger morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the second finger, also known as the index finger.

nodes.label: Abnormal 3rd finger morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the third finger.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the biliary system
nodes.def: An abnormality of the biliary system.

nodes.label: Short stature
nodes.def: A height below that which is expected according to age and gender norms. Although there is no universally accepted definition of short stature, many refer to "short stature" as height more than 2 standard deviations below the mean for age and gender (or below the 3rd percentile for age and gender dependent norms).

nodes.label: Decreased body weight
nodes.def: Abnormally low body weight.

nodes.label: Abnormal glycosphingolipid metabolism
nodes.def: An abnormality of glycosphingolipid metabolism.

nodes.label: Crossed fused renal ectopia
nodes.def: A developmental anomaly in which the kidneys are fused and localized on the same side of the midline. This anomaly is thought to result from disruption of the normal embryologic migration of the kidneys.

nodes.label: Fused cervical vertebrae
nodes.def: A congenital anomaly characterized by a joining (fusion) of two or more cervical vertebral bodies with one another.

nodes.label: Bowing of the legs
nodes.def: A bending or abnormal curvature affecting a long bone of the leg.

nodes.label: Myopathy
nodes.def: A disorder of muscle unrelated to impairment of innervation or neuromuscular junction.

nodes.label: Increased circulating IgG concentration
nodes.def: An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin G in blood.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the coagulation cascade
nodes.def: An abnormality of the coagulation cascade, which is comprised of the contact activation pathway (also known as the intrinsic pathway) and the tissue factor pathway (also known as the extrinsic pathway) as well as cofactors and regulators.

nodes.label: Recurrent gram-negative bacterial infections
nodes.def: Increased susceptibility to infection by gram-negative bacteria, as manifested by a medical history of repeated or frequent infections by these agents.

nodes.label: Abnormal intervertebral disk morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the intervertebral disk.

nodes.label: Abnormality of dental eruption
nodes.def: An abnormality of tooth eruption.

nodes.label: Abnormal femoral metaphysis morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the femoral metaphysis.

nodes.label: Aplasia/hypoplasia involving forearm bones
nodes.def: Absence (due to failure to form) or underdevelopment of one or more forearm bones.

nodes.label: Abnormal pyramidal sign
nodes.def: Functional neurological abnormalities related to dysfunction of the pyramidal tract.

nodes.label: Abnormality of somatosensory evoked potentials
nodes.def: An abnormality of somatosensory evoked potentials (SSEP), i.e., of the electrical signals of sensation going from the body to the brain in response to a defined stimulus. Recording electrodes are placed over the scalp, spine, and peripheral nerves proximal to the stimulation site. Clinical studies generally use electrical stimulation of peripheral nerves to elicit potentials. SSEP testing determines whether peripheral sensory nerves are able to transmit sensory information like pain, temperature, and touch to the brain. Abnormal SSEPs can result from dysfunction at the level of the peripheral nerve, plexus, spinal root, spinal cord, brain stem, thalamocortical projections, or primary somatosensory cortex.

nodes.label: Neoplasm of the genitourinary tract
nodes.def: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the genitourinary system.

nodes.label: Meningocele
nodes.def: Protrusion of the meninges through a defect of the skull or vertebral column.

nodes.label: Distal muscle weakness
nodes.def: Reduced strength of the musculature of the distal extremities.

nodes.label: Primitive reflex
nodes.def: The primitive reflexes are a group of behavioral motor responses which are found in normal early development, are subsequently inhibited, but may be released from inhibition by cerebral, usually frontal, damage. They are thus part of a broader group of reflexes which reflect release phenomena, such as exaggerated stretch reflexes and extensor plantars. They do however involve more complex motor responses than such simple stretch reflexes, and are often a normal feature in the neonate or infant.

nodes.label: Gastrointestinal arteriovenous malformation
nodes.def: An anomalous configuration of blood vessels that shunts arterial blood directly into veins without passing through the capillaries and that is located in the gastrointestinal tract.

nodes.label: Abnormal pelvic girdle bone morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the bony pelvic girdle, which is a ring of bones connecting the vertebral column to the femurs.

nodes.label: Recurrent bacterial infections
nodes.def: Increased susceptibility to bacterial infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of bacterial infection.

nodes.label: Osteoarthritis
nodes.def: Degeneration (wear and tear) of articular cartilage, i.e., of the joint surface. Joint degeneration may be accompanied by osteophytes (bone overgrowth), narrowing of the joint space, regions of sclerosis at the joint surface, or joint deformity.

nodes.label: Abnormal tarsal ossification
nodes.def: An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of any of the tarsal bones, seven bones of the foot comprising the calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, and the cuneiform bones.

nodes.label: Paralysis
nodes.def: Paralysis of voluntary muscles means loss of contraction due to interruption of one or more motor pathways from the brain to the muscle fibers. Although the word paralysis is often used interchangeably to mean either complete or partial loss of muscle strength, it is preferable to use paralysis or plegia for complete or severe loss of muscle strength, and paresis for partial or slight loss. Motor paralysis results from deficits of the upper motor neurons (corticospinal, corticobulbar, or subcorticospinal). Motor paralysis is often accompanied by an impairment in the facility of movement.

nodes.label: Foam cells
nodes.def: The presence of foam cells, a type of macrophage that localizes to fatty deposits on blood vessel walls, where they ingest low-density lipoproteins and become laden with lipids, giving them a foamy appearance.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphyses of the elbow
Disproportionate short-limb short stature
nodes.def: A type of disproportionate short stature characterized by a short limbs but an average-sized trunk.

nodes.label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the femoral head and neck
Atrioventricular canal defect
nodes.def: A defect of the atrioventricular septum of the heart.

nodes.label: Ulnar deviation of finger
nodes.def: Bending or curvature of a finger toward the ulnar side (i.e., away from the thumb). The deviation is at the metacarpal-phalangeal joint, and this finding is distinct from clinodactyly.

nodes.label: Radial deviation of finger
nodes.def: Bending or curvature of a finger toward the radial side (i.e., towards the thumb). The deviation is at the metacarpal-phalangeal joint, and this finding is distinct from clinodactyly.

nodes.label: Joint contracture of the hand
nodes.def: Contractures of one ore more joints of the hands meaning chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in non-bony tissue.

nodes.label: Deviation of the thumb
nodes.def: Displacement of the thumb from its normal position.

nodes.label: Abnormal epididymis morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the epididymis.

nodes.label: Triangular shaped phalanges of the hand
Abnormal pupillary function
nodes.def: A functional abnormality of the pupil.

nodes.label: Opacification of the corneal stroma
nodes.def: Reduced transparency of the stroma of cornea.

nodes.label: Abnormality of macular pigmentation
nodes.def: Abnormality of macular or foveal pigmentation.

nodes.label: Ichthyosis
nodes.def: An abnormality of the skin characterized the presence of excessive amounts of dry surface scales on the skin resulting from an abnormality of keratinization.

nodes.label: Abnormality of hair pigmentation
nodes.def: An abnormality of hair pigmentation (color).

nodes.label: Duplication of phalanx of 2nd finger
nodes.def: This term applies if one or more of the phalanges of the 2nd finger are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

nodes.label: Duplication of phalanx of 3rd finger
nodes.def: This term applies if one or more of the phalanges of the 3rd finger are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

nodes.label: Duplication of phalanx of 4th finger
nodes.def: This term applies if one or more of the phalanges of the 4th finger are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

nodes.label: Duplication of phalanx of 5th finger
nodes.def: This term applies if one or more of the phalanges of the 5th finger are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

nodes.label: Complete duplication of the proximal phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: A complete duplication affecting one or more of the proximal phalanges of the hand. As opposed to a partial duplication were there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones, a complete duplication leads to two separate bones appearing side to side (radio-ulnar axis) as seen on x-rays. A duplication leading to an accessory bone appearing in the proximo-distal axis on x-rays, this is actually a different entity called a Pseudoepiphyses (see according terms) sometimes also referred to as Hyperphalangism.

nodes.label: Complete duplication of the distal phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: A complete duplication affecting one or more of the distal phalanges of the hand.

nodes.label: Complete duplication of the middle phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: A complete duplication affecting one or more of the middle phalanges of the hand. As opposed to a partial duplication were there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones, a complete duplication leads to two separate bones appearing side to side (radio-ulnar axis) as seen on x-rays. A duplication leading to an accessory bone appearing in the proximo-distal axis on x-rays, this is actually a different entity called a pseudoepiphysis (see corresponding terms) sometimes also referred to as hyperphalangism.

nodes.label: Partial duplication of the proximal phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: A partial duplication, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance, affecting one or more of the proximal phalanges of the hand. As opposed to a complete duplication there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones.

nodes.label: Partial duplication of the distal phalanges of the hand
